HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 642
By Maberry
A RESOLUTION to commend Doug Englen for his honorable and
astute service as Chairman of the Montgomery
County Republican Party.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
specially recognize those estimable public servants who have dedicated themselves to
improving the quality of life for their fellow citizens; and
WHEREAS, one such remarkable individual is Doug Englen, whose legacy of service
spans over three decades in the United States Army and through continued civic leadership as
Chairman of the Montgomery County Republican Party; and
WHEREAS, after a storied military career, Mr. Englen entered the political arena as a
candidate for the Tennessee State Senate in District 22 in early 2020; though unsuccessful in
that race, he emerged as a dedicated public servant, consistently supporting his former
opponent and remaining actively engaged in Tennessee politics; and
WHEREAS, as Montgomery County Republican Party Chairman and the District 22
State Executive Committeeman, Doug Englen has exemplified servant leadership, guiding and
supporting conservative principles and candidates at the grassroots level; and
WHEREAS, from 2020 to 2024, he served as chapter president of the Tennessee
Firearms Association, sat on the board of the chamber of commerce, and chaired numerous
veterans' organizations, always striving to better his community through meaningful
engagement and advocacy; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Englen joined Bell in 2020 as the Fort Campbell representative for
Future Vertical Lift programs; drawing on his extensive aviation background, he advises on the
design, development, build, and test of the V-280 Valor aircraft for the United States Army's
Future Long Range Assault Aircraft program, contributing to the Army's modernization strategy;
and
