WHEREAS, prior to joining Bell, Doug Englen honorably served his nation as an active-
duty member of the United States Army for thirty-three years; in his final assignment, he served
as Senior Warrant Officer Advisor to the Chief of Staff and Secretary of the Army at the
Pentagon, after having served twenty-two years in Special Operations Command, assuming
roles ranging from technology acquisition to chief aviator and flight lead; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Englen accumulated nearly 8,000 flight hours during his service,
carrying out more than 2,500 combat missions across the globe; his earlier assignments
included CH-47D operations in Germany and Korea, after beginning his Army career as a UH-
1H mechanic; and
WHEREAS, Doug Englen holds a bachelor's degree from Embry-Riddle Aeronautical
University; he received advanced military education through the Army War College, FAA
certifications, and completion of elite programs, including the Air Force Weapons School and
Marine Weapons and Tactics Instructor Course; and
WHEREAS, for his service to our country, Mr. Englen was awarded the Distinguished
Service Medal, two Silver Star medals, Legion of Merit, three Distinguished Flying Cross
medals, two Bronze Star Medals, two Meritorious Service Medals, nine Air Medal with Valor
Device (Numeral 8), four Army Commendation Medals, four Army Achievement Medals, Army
Good Conduct Medal, National Defense Service Medal (one Bronze Service Star), Southwest
Asia Service Medal (three Bronze Service Stars), Iraq Campaign Medal, Global War on
Terrorism Expeditionary Medal, Global War on Terrorism Service Medal, Humanitarian Medal,
NCO Professional Development Ribbon (Numeral 2) , Army Service Ribbon, Overseas Service
Ribbon (Numeral 5), Kuwait Liberation Medal (Saudi Arabia), NATO Medal (one Bronze Star),
Kuwait Liberation Medal (Government of Kuwait), Combat Action Badge, Master Army Aviator
Badge, Air Assault Badge, and the Parachutist Badge; and
WHEREAS, a devoted husband, father, and grandfather, Doug Englen enjoys the love
and support of his wife, Tina, and their children, Chris (Rachelle), Alexandria (John), Catheryn,
and Elizabeth, and four cherished grandchildren; and
- 2 - 007258

WHEREAS, Mr. Englen is wholly committed to the noble precepts of public service and
political engagement that have earned Tennessee recognition as the Volunteer State, and he
should be specially recognized; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we hereby commend Doug Englen for his honorable and astute service as
Chairman of the Montgomery County Republican Party and salute his unswerving commitment
to living the examined life with courage and conviction.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
